# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version ^2.0.0 to dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` using npm

### 2. Integrated SpeedInsights Component
- Modified `frontend/src/App.tsx` to import and use the SpeedInsights component
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
- Placed the `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the TooltipProvider, after the SiteSettingsProvider
- This ensures the component is rendered at the app level and can track performance across all routes

## Files Modified
- `frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `frontend/package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for React applications:
- Used the React-specific package import: `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Component is placed at the root level of the app to ensure it tracks all page navigations
- No additional configuration required - the component works out of the box

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully - no compilation errors
✅ Linter passed - no new linting errors introduced (all 11 existing errors are pre-existing)
✅ Tests passed - 1 test suite passed (1/1)
✅ Package installed successfully with npm

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Speed Insights on Vercel:
1. Deploy this code to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Vercel dashboard
3. Select your project and go to Speed Insights in the sidebar
4. Click "Enable" to activate the feature
5. After deployment, Speed Insights will automatically start collecting performance metrics

The tracking script will be injected at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` and will begin collecting Core Web Vitals and other performance metrics once enabled in the Vercel dashboard.

## Technical Notes
- The project uses Vite 8.0.3 with React 18.3.1
- Package manager: npm
- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and won't impact bundle size significantly
- Component placement ensures it's active across all routes including admin panel
